2.3. Robust MAP Prior
When considering the use of historical controls in a new trial,
a careful selection of the historical trials is necessary to ren
der the exchangeability assumption for the control parameters
plausible. Pocock (1976) proposed criteria for the selection
process. Nevertheless, one has to acknowledge the possibility
of prior-data conflict. Hence we consider a robust version of
the MAP prior of Section 2.1, as
pHR(ψ) = (1−wR)pH(ψ)+wR pV(ψ) ,
(6)
where pH(ψ) is the approximated MAP prior, pV(ψ) isa
vague conjugate prior, and wR is the prior probability that
the new trial differs systematically from the historical trials.
The choice of wR could be based on the degree of confidence
of the clinical trial team in the relevance of the historical
data. Posterior summaries for several data scenarios or oper
